│ The function `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` checks  │
│ if the VPlan contains extra simplifications not accounted    │
│ for in the legacy cost model. It does this by comparing the  │
│ instructions in the loop with those in the VPlan. If there   │
│ are instructions in the loop that are not part of the VPlan  │
│ or are skipped for cost computation, it returns `true`.      │
│                                                              │
│ The assertion failure occurs because the                     │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` function is unable   │
│ to validate the discrepancy between the VPlan-based cost     │
│ model and the legacy cost model. To fix this, we need to     │
│ modify the assertion to account for cases where the          │
│ VPlan-based cost model selects a lower-cost VF, even if      │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` cannot validate the  │
│ discrepancy.                                                 │
│                                                              │
│ I will now propose a fix for this issue.                     │
